import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

1. Description of the problem

We are given a set of nodes, each defined by its x and y coordinates and an associated cost. The task is to select exactly half of the nodes (rounded up if the number is odd) and construct a Hamiltonian cycle that visits each selected node exactly once and returns to the starting node. The objective is to minimize the total sum of both the path length (computed using rounded Euclidean distances between nodes) and the costs of the selected nodes.

2. Pseudocode of implemented algorithms

2.1. Data

Input:

  • $n$: total number of nodes
  • $nodes[i] = (x_i, y_i, cost_i)$ for $i \in [0, n-1]$: array with all nodes
  • $distanceMatrix[i][j] = \text{round}\!\left(\sqrt{(x_i - x_j)^2 + (y_i - y_j)^2}\right)$: euclidean distance between i-th and j-th node

Output:

  • $route$: list of nodes forming a closed Hamiltonian cycle
  • $totalCost = \text{distance cost} + \text{node costs}$

2.2. Pure 2-Regret Greedy Cycle Heuristic

function solve(startIndex):

    n  number of nodes
    route  [startIndex]
    used[startIndex]  true

    bestSecond  argmin_j (distance[startIndex][j] + nodes[j].cost), j not used
    route.add(bestSecond)
    used[bestSecond]  true

    while size(route) < targetCount:
        bestNode, bestPos, bestRegret  -1, -1, -

        for each unused node j:
            deltas  []
            for pos in 0 .. size(route)-1:
                i  route[pos]
                k  route[(pos+1) mod size(route)]
                deltas.add(distance[i][j] + distance[j][k] - distance[i][k] + nodes[j].cost)

            sorted  sorted(deltas)
            best  sorted[0]
            regret  sum(sorted[m] - best for m=1..min(k-1, size(sorted)-1))

            if regret > bestRegret:
                bestRegret  regret
                bestNode  j
                bestPos  index(best in deltas) + 1

        insert bestNode at bestPos in route
        used[bestNode]  true

    route.add(startIndex)
    return Result(route, computeTotalCost(route))

2.3. Weighted Sum 2-Regret Greedy Cycle Heuristic

function solve(startIndex):

    n  number of nodes
    route  [startIndex]
    used[startIndex]  true

    bestSecond  argmin_j (distance[startIndex][j] + nodes[j].cost), j not used
    route.add(bestSecond)
    used[bestSecond]  true

    while size(route) < targetCount:
        bestNode, bestPos, bestScore  -1, -1, -

        for each unused node j:
            deltas  []
            for pos in 0 .. size(route)-1:
                i  route[pos]
                k  route[(pos+1) mod size(route)]
                deltas.add(distance[i][j] + distance[j][k] - distance[i][k] + nodes[j].cost)

            sorted  sorted(deltas)
            best  sorted[0]
            regret  sum(sorted[m] - best for m=1..min(k-1, size(sorted)-1))
            score  regretWeight * regret - (1 - regretWeight) * best

            if score > bestScore:
                bestScore  score
                bestNode  j
                bestPos  index(best in deltas) + 1

        insert bestNode at bestPos in route
        used[bestNode]  true

    route.add(startIndex)
    return Result(route, computeTotalCost(route))

2.4. Pure 2-Regret Flexible Nearest Neighbour Heuristic

function solve(startIndex):
    route  [startIndex]
    used[startIndex]  true

    while size(route) < targetCount:
        bestNode, bestPos, bestRegret  -1, -1, -

        for each unused node j:
            deltas  []
            for pos in 0 .. size(route):
                if pos == 0:
                    k  route[0]
                    delta  distance[j][k] + nodes[j].cost
                else if pos == size(route):
                    i  route[last]
                    delta  distance[i][j] + nodes[j].cost
                else:
                    i  route[pos-1]
                    k  route[pos]
                    delta  distance[i][j] + distance[j][k] - distance[i][k] + nodes[j].cost
                deltas.add(delta)
            deltas  sorted(deltas)
            best, second  deltas[0], deltas[1]
            regret  second - best

            if regret > bestRegret:
                bestRegret  regret
                bestNode  j
                bestPos  position of best in deltas

        insert bestNode at bestPos in route
        used[bestNode]  true

    route.add(route[0])
    return Result(route, totalCost(route))

2.5. Weighted Sum 2-Regret Flexible Nearest Neighbour Heuristic

function solve(startIndex):
    route  [startIndex]
    used[startIndex]  true

    while size(route) < targetCount:
        bestNode, bestPos, bestScore  -1, -1, -

        for each unused node j:
            deltas  []
            for pos in 0 .. size(route):
                if pos == 0:
                    k  route[0]
                    delta  distance[j][k] + nodes[j].cost
                else if pos == size(route):
                    i  route[last]
                    delta  distance[i][j] + nodes[j].cost
                else:
                    i  route[pos-1]
                    k  route[pos]
                    delta  distance[i][j] + distance[j][k] - distance[i][k] + nodes[j].cost
                deltas.add(delta)
            deltas  sorted(deltas)
            best, second  deltas[0], deltas[1]
            regret  second - best
            score  regretWeight * regret - (1 - regretWeight) * best

            if score > bestScore:
                bestScore  score
                bestNode  j
                bestPos  position of best in deltas

        insert bestNode at bestPos in route
        used[bestNode]  true

    route.add(route[0])
    return Result(route, totalCost(route))

def plot_tsp(tsp, solution, title):
    unused_nodes = np.array(set(tsp.index).difference(solution))
    X = tsp['x'].loc[solution].values
    Y = tsp['y'].loc[solution].values
    costs = tsp['cost'].loc[solution].values

    X_unused = tsp['x'].loc[unused_nodes].values
    Y_unused = tsp['y'].loc[unused_nodes].values
    costs_unused = tsp['cost'].loc[unused_nodes].values

    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 9))
    plt.scatter(X, Y, s=costs, color='red', alpha=0.4, label='Data points')
    plt.scatter(X_unused, Y_unused, s=costs_unused, color="grey", alpha=0.4, label="Unused nodes")
    plt.scatter(X, Y, color='blue')
    plt.title(title)
    plt.xlabel('X')
    plt.ylabel('Y')

    plt.plot(X, Y, color='blue', linestyle='-', linewidth=2, label='Connecting line')

8. Conclusions

  1. Implemented heuristics are more computationally expensive than ones from previous labs
  2. Heuristics based on greedy cycle and flexible NN had comparable performance
  3. Pure regret heuristics (i. e. heuristics where only regret was taken into account) had poor performance (even worse than most of heuristics from previous labs)
  4. Heuristics with weighted regret had better performance than ones without it (labs 1)
